- **CRITICAL: Use Context7 MCP for Library Documentation** - ALWAYS use Context7 MCP tools before web search
  - **Why**: Context7 provides up-to-date, accurate library documentation with code examples directly from official sources
  - **When to use**: Any time you need to understand how to use a library, framework, or package (e.g., "How do I use useMutation in convex-svelte?")
  - **Process**: 
    1. First: Call `mcp_context7_resolve-library-id` to find the library
    2. Then: Call `mcp_context7_get-library-docs` with the resolved library ID and your specific topic
    3. Only if Context7 fails or doesn't have the library: Fall back to web search
  - **Never**: Search the web for library documentation when Context7 is available
  - **Examples**: convex-svelte, Svelte, Tailwind, Bits UI, etc. - check Context7 first!
- use our /dev-docs folder for guides and keep them up to date
- **CRITICAL: Design Token System** - ALWAYS use semantic tokens instead of numeric/hardcoded Tailwind classes
  - **Spacing Tokens**: NEVER use `px-2`, `py-1.5`, `gap-2` etc. - use `px-nav-item`, `py-nav-item`, `gap-icon`, `px-menu-item`, `px-badge`, `px-header`, etc.
  - **Color Tokens**: NEVER use `bg-gray-900`, `text-white`, `text-gray-300` etc. - use `bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar-primary`, `text-sidebar-secondary`, `border-sidebar`, `hover:bg-sidebar-hover`, etc.
  - **Typography Tokens**: NEVER use `text-[10px]` - use `text-label` instead
  - **Why**: All tokens automatically adapt to light/dark mode and can be changed globally by updating ONE CSS variable in `src/app.css`
  - **Before adding**: Check `dev-docs/design-tokens.md` for available tokens
  - **If missing**: Add new token to `src/app.css` @theme block first, then create @utility class, then document in `dev-docs/design-tokens.md`
- follow our design tokens system - check `dev-docs/design-tokens.md` before creating new UI components
- use design tokens (spacing, typography, colors) from our system instead of arbitrary values
- when a pattern repeats 3+ times, document it in `dev-docs/design-tokens.md` before extracting to components
